> Radio Shack has a nifty little ratchet wrench that takes 1/4 inch hex
> ended bits... NOT a heavy duty tool but useful for tight spaces where
> even a stubby screwdriver might not fit...It's in the Boy-when-you-need-
> this-you-really-need-this tray in my tool box... ;-)

You can also use a small socket ratchet because those bits fit into one of
the small fractional sockets. I've used this to remove the screws on the
dash by the window and the aluminum trim holding the canvas down.

